videos.title: Foundation: The Real Identity Of The Robot Behind Kalle Revealed
videos.description:
When Foundation season 3 closed on that breathtaking lunar reveal, fans felt the world tilt. There stood Kalley, finally out in the open after being a whispered presence through the season, and beside her‚Äîa robot unlike any we‚Äôd seen in the show so far. No attempt at blending in, no human-like skin stretched over a frame. This was raw metal, all edges and unmistakably mechanical lines. It wasn‚Äôt a clone like the Cleons. It wasn‚Äôt D√©merzel, hiding her nature under humaniform grace. This was a callback to something older, something rooted deep in Asimov‚Äôs Robot novels. And for book readers, only one name came to mind: Giskard.

It‚Äôs no exaggeration to say that Giskard Reventlov is one of the most important figures in Asimov‚Äôs entire shared universe. Without him, the bridge between the Robot stories and the Foundation saga doesn‚Äôt exist. Without him, the Zeroth Law‚Äîthe principle that justifies robots interfering with humanity‚Äôs destiny‚Äînever would have been born. Without him, even Daneel himself wouldn‚Äôt have had the tools or the conviction to guide humanity for twenty thousand years. Giskard may not always be in the spotlight in the novels, but his shadow stretches across the entire arc of the galaxy.

videos.title: 7 DETALHES QUE VOC√ä N√ÉO VIU SOBRE O FILME Cidade de Deus ( 2002 )
Foundation: Why Kalle And The Robots Are Hiding On Earth's Moon Explained
videos.description:
The ending of Foundation season 3 gave us one of those moments that lingers long after the credits roll. A quiet moonlit shot, Kalley standing beside a robot, Earth hanging like a jewel in the distance. And then her calm words: ‚Äúall the pieces are in place.‚Äù It wasn‚Äôt loud or flashy, but it landed with more weight than a dozen space battles. Because if she‚Äôs been there all this time, hidden on the moon of Earth, then what exactly has she been doing‚Äîand why now? Why step forward only when everything else is collapsing? Let‚Äôs dig deep, because the clues are scattered everywhere. What she and her companion have been up to isn‚Äôt just background noise; it‚Äôs the slow heartbeat underneath the entire story.

The first thing to understand is that their absence was never really absence. Just because we didn‚Äôt see them doesn‚Äôt mean they weren‚Äôt present. Their fingerprints are all over the story, even if most characters didn‚Äôt realize it.

Press Release:

Today, Apple TV+ unveiled the thrilling trailer for the third season of ‚ÄúFoundation,‚Äù the epic hit saga from storyteller David S. Goyer. Based on Isaac Asimov‚Äôs award-winning stories and led by Emmy-nominated actors Jared Harris, Lee Pace and star Lou Llobell, the 10-episode season will debut globally with one episode on Friday, July 11 on Apple TV+, followed by new episodes weekly, every Friday through September 12. The Apple Original drama is produced for Apple TV+ by Skydance Television. 

About Isaac Asimov:
Isaac Asimov was an American writer and professor of biochemistry at Boston University. He was known for his science fiction and popular science works. Asimov was a prolific writer who wrote or edited more than 500 books. 

Asimov wrote hard science fiction. Along with Robert A. Heinlein and Arthur C. Clarke, he was considered one of the "Big Three" science fiction writers during his lifetime. His most famous work is the Foundation series, the first three books of which won the one-time Hugo Award for "Best All-Time Series" in 1966.

videos.title: What Vibe Coders Wish They Knew Sooner
videos.description:
Join me as I chat with Cody Schneider about the power of using YouTube Creators for influencer marketing. Cody explains a step-by-step playbook for acquiring customers through YouTube creator partnerships. The strategy involves reaching out to 100+ creators in your niche, offering a three-video package plus affiliate commission, identifying which creators drive the most conversions, then putting top performers on monthly retainers. This creates a scalable system where you eventually have dozens of creators regularly making content about your product, with trackable ROI through affiliate links.

Timestamps:
00:00 - Intro
01:03 - Why partner with Youtube Creators
04:38 - How to find and contact YouTube creators
08:11 - Crafting the email and follow-up strategy
09:26 - Overview of the Strategy
14:42 - The value of underpriced attention
19:12 - The numbers and scaling the process
22:06 - Biggest Bottleneck
22:50 - Automating the process
24:47 - Why start now

Key Points:
‚Ä¢ YouTube creators + affiliate marketing is an effective strategy for getting initial customers, especially for SMB products with one standout feature 
‚Ä¢ The strategy works by reaching out to creators, having them make videos about your product, and giving them affiliate commissions 
‚Ä¢ This is a marketing arbitrage opportunity because many smaller creators (10k-50k subscribers) don't know how to properly price themselves 
‚Ä¢ The goal is to identify underpriced creators, test them, then put the best performers on retainer to create monthly content

1) The YouTube Creator + Affiliate Marketing Strategy

This approach is PERFECT for:
‚Ä¢ SaaS products with one standout feature
‚Ä¢ SMB-focused tools
‚Ä¢ Products that solve specific pain points

The concept? Get YouTube creators to demo your product in their videos + give them affiliate commissions.

2) Why This Strategy Works So Well

It's an INEFFICIENT MARKET opportunity:

‚Ä¢ Smaller creators (10K-50K subs) often don't know their true value
‚Ä¢ You can find creators dramatically underpricing themselves
‚Ä¢ Unlike short-form content, you can track EXACT ROI through affiliate links
‚Ä¢ The content is evergreen and keeps driving customers

"I have a friend that took his company from zero to six million ARR in 18 months only running this strategy." - Cody

3) Step 1: Finding The Right Creators

Here's how to build your creator list:

‚Ä¢ Search YouTube for topics related to your product niche
‚Ä¢ Filter for 4-20 minute videos (longer form content)
‚Ä¢ Look for creators already making content in your category
‚Ä¢ Focus on engagement (likes/comments) over just subscriber count


4) Step 2: The Perfect Outreach Email

The EXACT template that works:

Subject: paid collaboration

"Hey, I love the content you're posting on YouTube.

Can I get a cost breakdown for a three video package and I'll give you an affiliate commission of 30%?"

Then follow up 10+ times (seriously!) - creators get bombarded with messages.

5) Why Three Videos Instead of One?

This is strategic genius:

‚Ä¢ One video = flash in the pan
‚Ä¢ Three videos = establishes credibility with their audience
‚Ä¢ Spread them over 6-8 weeks mixed with their regular content
‚Ä¢ Viewers think "this creator ACTUALLY uses this tool"

The affiliate commission creates long-term alignment and prevents price increases later!

6) Finding The Underpriced Attention

When you reach out to 100 creators:
‚Ä¢ About 50 will respond
‚Ä¢ ~10 will dramatically underprice themselves
‚Ä¢ 2-3 will drive 80% of your revenue

The key metric: Cost of 3-video package √∑ Subscribers (or avg views)

This helps you identify which creators offer the best ROI.

7) Scaling The System

Here's the compounding growth strategy:

‚Ä¢ Start with 100 outreach emails
‚Ä¢ Work with the 10 best-priced creators
‚Ä¢ Identify the 2-3 top performers
‚Ä¢ Put them on monthly retainers
‚Ä¢ REPEAT the process with 100 new creators


8) The Viral Flywheel Effect

The magic happens when:
‚Ä¢ One of your sponsored videos goes viral
‚Ä¢ Other creators make videos about that viral video
‚Ä¢ They join your affiliate program too
‚Ä¢ Your product gets "astroturfed" across the entire ecosystem

Meu equipamento tem um plugue mais grosso, de 20A e n√£o entra em minha tomada de 10A que tem furos mais finos. Posso simplesmente trocar a tomada de 10 por uma de 20A? E as demais tomadas de minha casa? Posso usar 20A em tudo? 

No Brasil existem dois tipos de tomadas residenciais: a tomada de 10A e a tomada de 20A. As tomadas de 20A s√£o aquelas famosas por ter o furo maior, capaz de receber um pino mais grosso.

Mas porque alguns equipamentos v√™m com esse pino? Isso est√° relacionado com a capacidade do equipamento. Se a corrente el√©trica necess√°ria para ele funcionar, passar de 10A, o fabricante j√° disponibiliza seu plugue com esta configura√ß√£o. 

Existem ainda alguns casos de equipamentos que tem corrente menor que 10A, por√©m muito pr√≥xima deste valor e neste caso tamb√©m possuem plugues de 20A. Os fabricantes de micro-ondas, fornos el√©tricos, torradeiras entre outros produtos j√° seguem rigorosamente este padr√£o de pino. O problema √© que muitas vezes, quando o produto chega a sua casa, √© aquela luta para achar a tomada adequada para ele. 

Em alguns casos as pessoas recorrem ao uso de um adaptador de 10 para 20A que nada mais √© do que um componente com pino fino de 10A em uma extremidade e furos grossos compat√≠veis com 20A na outra. Isso seria o mesmo que fazer a famosa gambiarra de aumentar o furo da tomada de 10 para colocar o pino de 20. Essas pr√°ticas devem ser evitadas. 

Mas ent√£o o que fazer neste caso? √â s√≥ trocar de 10 para 20A a tomada do local em que vou ligar o equipamento?

N√£o √© t√£o simples assim. √â preciso verificar se os circuitos est√£o corretamente dimensionados, ou seja, condutores e disjuntores perfeitamente calculados. E se seu equipamento tem corrente superior a 10A, voc√™ obrigatoriamente dever√° disponibilizar um circuito exclusivo para ele com condutores e disjuntores corretamente dimensionados, desde o quadro de distribui√ß√£o at√© a tomada.

Ser√° que a troca das tomadas de 10 para 20A pode ser feita em todos os pontos de uma resid√™ncia? A resposta definitiva para essa pergunta √©: SIM. Mas vamos ver o porqu√™.

A norma NBR-14136 que regulamenta a fabrica√ß√£o dos pinos e tomadas no Brasil √© muito clara quanto a isso. No seu item 3.2 ‚Äì Compatibilidade, ela diz que as tomadas de 20 A devem permitir a inser√ß√£o de plugues de 10 A e 20 A, e as tomadas com contato terra devem permitir a inser√ß√£o de plugues com e sem pino terra. 

Fica claro que os fabricantes s√£o obrigados a disponibilizar as tomadas de 20A com capacidade para receber os pinos de 10A sem preju√≠zo da conex√£o. N√≥s j√° testamos as tomadas da Pial Legrand aqui no canal e mostramos que elas atendem perfeitamente, mas sabemos que existem outros fabricantes conhecidos e s√©rios que possuem tomadas seguindo as recomenda√ß√µes normativas, o problema √© que tamb√©m sabemos que existe a possibilidade de voc√™ comprar uma tomada que n√£o tenha tanta qualidade e ao usar o pino fino em fura√ß√£o maior, isso acaba criando um mau contato com o passar do tempo, ent√£o todo cuidado √© pouco. 

Al√©m do cuidado na escolha do produto, para fazer essa troca √© preciso verificar se os circuitos est√£o corretamente dimensionados, ou seja, condutores e disjuntores perfeitamente calculados.

¬øQUI√âN ES CARLITOS? (WHO'S CARLITOS?)

Carlos Alberto C√°zares Valenzuela tiene 20 a√±os (en 2024) y naci√≥ en Mexicali, Baja California Norte (M√©xico). Cuando ten√≠a un a√±o de edad su familia se mud√≥ a Ciudad Obreg√≥n, donde vive con su mam√°, pap√° y su hermana.

El apodo de ‚ÄúEl Solovino‚Äù se lo puso el conductor de televisi√≥n Javier Rodr√≠guez ‚ÄúA√±i√±√≠‚Äù, quien ten√≠a un programa de m√∫sica en Televisora Grupo Pac√≠fico, emisi√≥n a la que acud√≠a Carlitos solo con la intenci√≥n de bailar, el locutor dec√≠a "solo vino", y fue as√≠ como despu√©s lo nombro ‚ÄúEl Solovino‚Äù.

Carlitos vino al mundo condicionado por retraso tiroide sublingual, padecimiento que le impide hablar con fluidez.

‚ÄúLos doctores me dijeron que iba a quedar de talla peque√±a y que no iba crecer‚Äù, comparti√≥ la se√±ora Hilda Valenzuela, mam√° del bailar√≠n m√°s famosos de las redes sociales.

‚ÄúCarlitos camin√≥ hasta los dos a√±os, pero cuando escuchaba m√∫sica se mov√≠a sentado, pues desde chico mostr√≥ que la m√∫sica era algo que le gustaba‚Äù, mencion√≥ su madre.

Su condici√≥n le impidi√≥ desarrollar su f√≠sico por completo, es por ello que es de estatura baja, pero su talento y carisma son enormes.

La mam√° de Carlitos lo describi√≥ como un hijo noble, trabajador e hiperactivo.

‚ÄúTemprano sale a la calle y va a los negocios a bailar, porque le encanta el baile, las monedas que gana las trae a la casa para que le haga unas entomatadas, que son su comida favorita, y adem√°s le encanta el refresco‚Äù, coment√≥ su madre.

Por su estado f√≠sico Carlitos no pudo culminar la secundaria, y revel√≥ que le gustar√≠a estudiar, pero su familia no cuenta con el recurso necesario para costear la formaci√≥n especial que requiere.

Carlitos tiene un proyecto, y es promover la discom√≥vil de su pap√° ‚ÄúLa Mentirosa‚Äù, es por ello que invita a la gente a que la contrate al celular +52 6442 28 25 84 y Carlitos y su familia puedan tener un ingreso que los permita salir adelante.

ENGLISH:
Carlos Alberto C√°zares Valenzuela is 20 years old (as of 2024) and was born in Mexicali, Baja California Norte (Mexico). When he was one year old his family moved to Ciudad Obreg√≥n, where he lives with his mother, father and sister.

The nickname ‚ÄúEl Solovino‚Äù (The Uninvited) was given to him by the television host Javier Rodr√≠guez ‚ÄúA√±i√±√≠‚Äù, who had a music program on Televisora Grupo Pac√≠fico where Carlitos arrived alone with the only intention of dancing. The announcer said "he came uninvited", and that's how he later called him ‚ÄúThe uninvited.‚Äù

Carlitos came into the world conditioned by sublingual thyroid delay, a condition that prevents him from speaking fluently.

‚ÄúThe doctors told me that he was going to be small and that he would not grow,‚Äù shared Mrs. Hilda Valenzuela, mother of the most famous dancer on social networks.

‚ÄúCarlitos walked until he was two years old, but when he listened to music he moved while sitting, because from a young age he showed that music was something he liked,‚Äù told his mother.

His condition prevented him from fully developing his physique, which is why he is short, but his talent and charisma are enormous.

Carlitos' mother described him as a noble, hard-working and hyperactive son.

‚ÄúEarly in the morning he goes to the shops to dance, because he loves dancing, the coins he earns he brings home so I can make him some entomatadas, his favorite food, and he also loves soda,‚Äù commented his mother.

Due to his physical condition, Carlitos was not able to finish high school, and he revealed that he would like to study, but his family does not have the necessary resources to pay for the special training he requires.

Carlitos has a project, and it is to promote his father's mobile disco ‚ÄúLa Mentirosa‚Äù, which is why he invites people to hire it at the cell phone +52 6442 28 25 84, so that Carlitos and his family can have an income that allows them to get ahead.

videos.title: The Genius Of RUSH's "Tom Sawyer" (Neil Peart)
videos.description:
"Tom Sawyer" is a drummer‚Äôs dream, showcasing Neil Peart‚Äôs unmatched skill and creativity. From the instantly recognizable intro hi-hat groove to the intricate 7/8 groove during the keyboard solo, and the explosive drum solo that follows, Peart‚Äôs performance on this track is a masterclass in drumming. It‚Äôs a perfect example of why he earned the nickname "The Professor‚Äù.

Featured as the opening track on RUSH's 1981 album 'Moving Pictures,' "Tom Sawyer" was the song that propelled the band into the mainstream. It marked a pivotal moment in their career, following the more radio-friendly direction they began with their previous album 'Permanent Waves'. The band‚Äôs ability to blend progressive rock with more accessible, radio-friendly hooks resonated with a global audience, and "Tom Sawyer" became one of their most enduring hits.

Join Drumeo‚Äôs Brandon Toews as he breaks down what makes Neil Peart‚Äôs drumming on "Tom Sawyer" so legendary, exploring the intricate grooves, complex drum fills, and the explosive drum solo that continues to inspire drummers worldwide‚Äîmore than forty years later.

Nixian Channel Description:

We‚Äôre lifelong video game enthusiasts with a passion for showing the world how our favorite hobby has grown with us, from individual series to industry-wide retrospectives.

We put significant time and creative effort into each one of our videos, including research, digging into archives, recording voiceovers, and editing. Every video takes as many as 10 hours to produce, because we strive to give our fans consistent, high-quality content.

Our popular ‚ÄúEvolution of...‚Äù series goes far beyond simply presenting gameplay footage. We take the time to show how a video game property ‚Äî its gameplay, character designs, graphics, sound direction, etc. ‚Äî have evolved over time. We include unique voiceover work on each video to enhance the viewing experience.

People have been playing video games for decades. In that time, we‚Äôve gone from moving a white line up and down to block a moving pixel, to participating in full-fledged, painstakingly rendered real-time battles with people all over the world. We help older gamers look back on how these experiences have changed throughout their lives, and new gamers to understand the broader context of the series they‚Äôre playing for the first time today.
The video game medium never stops growing, and we‚Äôll never stop chronicling its evolution.
Editing and voice-over were made by me.

videos.title: A Century Later: Celebrating the Life of Percival Lowell, Part 1
videos.description:
100 years after his death we are celebrating our founder - World traveler, author, and scientist of a Boston Brahim clan, Lowell made transformative contributions in the fields of Astronomy and Orientology. His impact was far-reaching, from introducing the more and religious customs of Eastern cultures to the West, to founding an astronomical observatory that helped convert the town of Flagstaff, Arizona into a vibrant center of scientific research. 

2016 marks the 100th anniversary of Lowell's death, a touchstone year for exploring and evaluating Lowell's legacy.

videos.title: Kraftwerk live on ZDF, 1973
videos.description:
Kraftwerk (German: [Ààk Åaftv…õ…êÃØk], "power station") is a German band formed in D√ºsseldorf in 1970 by Ralf H√ºtter and Florian Schneider. Widely considered to be innovators and pioneers of electronic music, they were among the first successful acts to popularize the genre. The group began as part of West Germany's experimental krautrock scene in the early 1970s before embracing electronic instrumentation, including synthesizers, drum machines, vocoders, and self-made instruments, in the middle of the decade. On commercially successful albums such as Autobahn (1974), Trans-Europe Express (1977), and The Man-Machine (1978), Kraftwerk developed a self-described "robot pop" style that combined electronic music with pop melodies, sparse arrangements, and repetitive rhythms, while adopting a stylized image including matching suits.

The band‚Äôs work would exert a lasting and profound influence across many genres of modern music, including synthpop, hip hop, post-punk, techno, ambient, and club music, and inspired a wide and diverse range of artists. According to The Observer, "no other band since the Beatles has given so much to pop culture." Following the release of Electric Caf√© (1986), member Wolfgang Fl√ºr left the group in 1987. Their last album Tour de France Soundtracks was released in 2003. Founding member Schneider departed in 2008. In 2014, the Recording Academy honored Kraftwerk with a Grammy Lifetime Achievement Award. As of 2018, the remaining members of the band continue to tour.

videos.description:
Hello everyone, today I'm going to show you a delicious and simple Air Fryer Recipe with an Onion and a lid.
You'll only need a few ingredients! 

Ingredients:

- Large Onion: 1
- Ice cold water.
- Egg: 1.
- Milk: 50 ml / 1,7 fl oz.
- Flour: 100 g / 3,5 oz.
- Black pepper: 1/4 teaspoon.
- Sweet paprika: 1 teaspoon.
- Salt: 1 teaspoon.
- Breadcrumbs.
- Seed oil.

For the dipping sauce:

- Mayonnaise: 2 tablespoons.
- Sour cream or greek yogurt: 3 tablespoons.
- Ketchup: 1 teaspoon.
- Dried garlic: 1/4 teaspoon.
- Sweet paprika: 1/4 teaspoon.
- Dried chives: 1/2 teaspoon.
- Salt to taste.

In the Air fryer at 190 ¬∞C / 374 ¬∞F for 20 minutes.

videos.title: The quick and easy way to devein and peel shrimp using a simple bamboo skewer!
videos.description:
This is a really cool trick to quickly deveining shrimp without having to cut it open. 

Shrimp have their intestines which run along their back. These are full of shrimp poop and will make your shrimp taste bad when you eat them. So, you have to remove them.

Sometimes these intestines are referred to as "Sand Vein" to make it more appealing. But they're the poop shoots... So, you gotta remove them. 

By using a simple wooden skewer, I will show you how quick and easy it is to devein and peel shrimp without having to cut them open and ruin their nice, uniform shape.

videos.title: Build a RAG app using LangFlow + @streamlitofficial with minimal coding | LangFlow crash course
videos.description:
Can AI explain itself? In other words, if I take an AI model and ask it questions about any other AI model, I would expect it to answer my questions. But it turns out that the model simply doesn't know about any other models. Can a simple workaround for this problem lie with Retrieval Augmented Generation or RAG. 
I developed a chat app using LangFlow and StreamLit with minimal coding and solved this very problem. It uses a RAG pipeline in the backend. I provided the retrieval system with all the papers on the Phi series of models developed by Microsoft and eventually, the system was able to answer my questions about the Phi family of models. 

So in this video, I will walk you through how I went about developing the pipeline and along the way demonstrate how easy it is to develop a chat app using LangFlow.

videos.title: Isaac Asimov's Foundation Explained In FIVE Minutes! (Some Spoilers)
videos.description:
Isaac Asimov‚Äôs Foundation Series was the first-ever science fiction series to contain a full-fledged galactic empire. The entire series involves the centuries-long plan of a man known as Hari Seldon, to restore the human galactic empire after a great crash that led to a dark age. Hari Seldon was able to predict the fall of the first galactic empire by use of a form of mathematics known as psychohistory, which was able to predict human behavior overtime at mass. 

Essentially the empire fell due to the capital planet, Trantor's inability to adequately handle the bureaucratic and administrative demands of such a large empire, containing 25 Million worlds. Hari Seldon‚Äôs Solution would ultimately prove to be extremely complicated and multifaceted, but it is presented initially as the creation of the Foundation. The Foundation would be founded on the distant world of Terminus and would have an encyclopedist whose job was to record all human knowledge in the universe inside the Encyclopedia Galactica. Thousands of humans would devote themselves to the project in an effort to preserve the knowledge of all mankind in the hope that doing so they could shorten the interregnum which would follow the collapse of the empire.

step by step easy guide to backup your old video tapes to your computer using OBS Studio. 

You'll need the following:

1. VHS player

Navigate to EDIT, Audio Properties

For Desktop Audio under Audio Monitoring, select 'Monitor Only (Mute output),
for 
Mic|Aux, select 'Monitor and Output'
